{"metadata":{"title":"Preferences","modules":[{"name":"TUIkit"}],"role":"collectionGroup"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Pass data from child views up to their ancestors."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Preferences"},"sections":[],"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StateManagement","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ThemingGuide","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/FocusSystem","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StatusBarGuide","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/AppearanceAndColors","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/CustomViews","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/KeyboardShortcuts","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/PaletteReference","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ListAndTable","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/LayoutSystem"],"anchor":"Guides"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/tuikit\/preferences"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"TUIkit’s preference system enables ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"bottom-up data flow"}]},{"text":": the reverse of environment values. While the environment passes data down from parent to child, preferences let child views publish values that ancestors can observe and react to.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The system mirrors SwiftUI’s preference API and consists of three parts:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"PreferenceKey","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Protocol that defines a named value type with a default and a reduce st